devdoc.details: Contais the methods related to disputes. Tellor.sol references this library for function's logic.

beginDispute(OldTellorStorage.TellorStor.details: Helps initialize a dispute by assigning it a disputeId when a miner returns a false on the validate array(in Tellor.ProofOfWork) it sends the invalidated value information to POS voting

params._minerIndex: the index of the miner that submitted the value being disputed. Since each official value requires 5 miners to submit a value.

proposeFork(OldTellorStorage.TellorStora.details: Allows for a fork to be proposed

updateDisputeFee(OldTellorStorage.Tellor.details: this function allows the dispute fee to fluctuate based on the number of miners on the system. The floor for the fee is 15e18.

params._supportsDispute: is the vote (true=the dispute has basis false = vote against dispute)
